100 Years Ago Today, This is What Was Happening ...

On February 17, 1926, the League of Nations convened in Geneva, where discussions focused on disarmament and international peace, highlighting ongoing tensions in Europe. Meanwhile, in the United States, the Senate continued to debate the merits of Prohibition, with public sentiment increasingly swaying towards repeal. In the realm of science, American inventor Thomas Edison announced advancements in electric power generation, promising to revolutionize the industry.
